doc.ContractDescription: EXPOSING THE SECRET X-RAY LIVES OF CEPHEIDS WITH XMM-NEWTON THE MAIN GOALS ARE TO DETERMINE THE OR1G1N&NATURE OF PULSATION-INDUCED X-RAY (AND FUV) EMISSIONS DISCOVERED FROM THE ~RIGHT CLASSICAL CEPHEID BETA DOR . WHEN COMBINED WITH PREVIOUS X-RAY&FUV OBSERVATIONS, THIS PROGRAM WILL PROVIDE A CRITICAL TEST BED FOR STUDYING X-RAY GENERATION IN CEPHEIDS THAT WE WERE THE FIRST TO DISCOVER. OUR TARGET BETA DOR IS A 9.8-D PULSATING CEPHEID THAT SHOWS STRONGLY PHASED VARIABLE FUV LINE EMISSIONS AND X-RAY EMISSIONS. WE WILL CAREFULLY MEASURE THE X-RAY ENERGY DISTRIBUTIONS (USING -40 KSEC BINNING) THAT WILL PROVIDE EXCELLENT PULSATION PHASE RESOLUTION . WE WILL ANALYZE THE X-RAY DATA TO DETERMINE THE PHYSICAL PROPERTIES OF THE EMITTING PLASMAS, (SUCH AS LX, AND T) AND APPLY PULSATING-INDUCED SHOCK MODELS.
